{
  "id": "019d3339-9447-75c3-9b23-12ff66a9321a",
  "content": "# Inference Crash Pattern During corvia-dev Restart (2026-03-28)\n\n## Pattern\nWhen corvia-dev restarts rapidly (e.g., during spoke testing), the inference process:\n1. Loads embedding model (nomic-embed-text-v1.5) successfully\n2. Loads chat model (qwen3 via llama.cpp) successfully\n3. Crashes with exit code 1 approximately 4 seconds after chat model loads\n4. Manager restarts inference, but restarted process only starts gRPC server without reloading models\n5. All subsequent embedding requests fail with Model not loaded\n\n## Resolution\nClean restart after a settling period (3+ seconds between down and up) avoids the crash. The race condition appears related to rapid stop/start cycles where model memory is not fully released before the new process claims GPU resources.\n\n## Impact on Multi-Spoke\nSpoke testing requires server restarts (e.g., changing bind address). Must use clean restart pattern from CLAUDE.md: corvia-dev down, sleep 3, corvia-dev up.",
  "source_version": "mcp",
  "scope_id": "corvia",
